Title : The Battle to the Weak
Text : '''''The Battle to the Weak''''' is a [[novel]] by Welsh-born writer [[Hilda Vaughan]].

==Publication==
The Battle to the Weak was Vaughan's first novel, published in 1925.<ref name=wm>{{cite news |url=https://www.questia.com/read/1G1-242926678 |title=Reviews |work=Western Mail |date=27 November 2010 |accessdate=4 May 2014 |via=[[Questia Online Library]] |subscription=yes}}</ref>

==Reception==
According to Christopher Newman, though her literary technique would develop throughout her career, The Battle to the Weak contains "virtually all the themes developed in her later works", especially those of duty and self-sacrifice.<ref name="Newman p. 24.">Newman p. 24.</ref> The novel was very favourably received, with reviews noting the accomplished character of the work, in spite of it being her first.<ref name="Thomas 2008, p. 12.">Thomas 2008, p. 12.</ref> The [[Western Mail (Wales)|Western Mail]] said of it "Wales depicted truly at last."<ref name=wm/>

